searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Hackflare","doc":"Hackflare is a Cloudflare alternative built for HackClub.\n\nThis module serves as the top-level application context and provides the foundation\nfor the domain logic and business operations of the HackFlare DNS management system.","ref":"Hackflare.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Architecture - Hackflare","doc":"The Hackflare application is built on the PETRL stack:\n- **Phoenix** - Web framework for HTTP/WebSocket communication\n- **Elixir** - Functional language for business logic and OTP applications\n- **Tailwind** - Utility-first CSS framework for styling\n- **Rust** - Performance-critical DNS handling via native extensions\n- **LiveView** - Real-time interactive web components","ref":"Hackflare.html#module-architecture"},{"type":"module","title":"Key Components - Hackflare","doc":"","ref":"Hackflare.html#module-key-components"},{"type":"module","title":"Contexts - Hackflare","doc":"The application uses a context-based architecture where business logic is contained\nin separate modules. Each context manages its own data and state.","ref":"Hackflare.html#module-contexts"},{"type":"module","title":"Native Integration - Hackflare","doc":"DNS operations (nameserver, zone management, record handling) are implemented in Rust\nusing Rustler NIFs for maximum performance. The `Hackflare.Native` module provides\nthe bindings to these native functions.","ref":"Hackflare.html#module-native-integration"},{"type":"module","title":"Database - Hackflare","doc":"PostgreSQL is used via Ecto for persistent storage of domain, DNS record, and user data.\nSee `Hackflare.Repo` for database access.","ref":"Hackflare.html#module-database"},{"type":"module","title":"Running the Application - Hackflare","doc":"iex -S mix phx.server\n\nThis starts the Phoenix server with the IEx console, allowing interactive development.","ref":"Hackflare.html#module-running-the-application"},{"type":"module","title":"Hackflare.Application","doc":"The OTP Application entry point and supervision tree for Hackflare.\n\nThis module defines the supervision tree that starts all essential services\nfor the Hackflare application. It's called by the Elixir runtime on startup\nand supervises all child processes needed for the application to run.","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Supervision Tree - Hackflare.Application","doc":"The following services are started and supervised:\n\n- `Hackflare.Repo` - PostgreSQL database connection pool\n- `HackflareWeb.Telemetry` - Observability and metrics collection\n- `DNSCluster` - DNS cluster management for distributed deployments\n- `Hackflare.Nameserver` - DNS nameserver process handling DNS queries\n- `Hackflare.PubSub` - Phoenix PubSub for real-time communication\n- `HackflareWeb.Endpoint` - HTTP endpoint serving the web application","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#module-supervision-tree"},{"type":"module","title":"Strategy - Hackflare.Application","doc":"Uses `:one_for_one` supervision strategy, meaning if any child process crashes,\nonly that child is restarted, not the entire tree.","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#module-strategy"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Application.config_change/3","doc":"Called when application configuration changes at runtime.\n\nThis callback is invoked when the application configuration is updated during\nruntime (typically in development with hot reloading). It propagates configuration\nchanges to the Phoenix endpoint.","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#config_change/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Application.config_change/3","doc":"- `changed` - Keyword list of changed configs\n  - `_new` - New configuration values (unused)\n  - `removed` - List of removed configuration keys","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#config_change/3-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Application.config_change/3","doc":"`:ok` - Configuration change was applied successfully","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#config_change/3-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Application.start/2","doc":"Starts the Hackflare application and its supervision tree.\n\nThis callback is invoked by the Elixir runtime when the application is started.\nIt creates the supervision tree with all child processes and returns the root\nsupervisor's PID.","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#start/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Application.start/2","doc":"- `_type` - Application start type (`:normal`, `:transient`, or `:temporary`)\n  - `_args` - Arguments passed to the application (usually from mix/config)","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#start/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Application.start/2","doc":"- `{:ok, pid}` - PID of the root supervisor\n  - `{:error, reason}` - If supervision tree startup fails","ref":"Hackflare.Application.html#start/2-returns"},{"type":"module","title":"Hackflare.Mailer","doc":"Email service for Hackflare using Swoosh.\n\nThis module provides email sending capabilities for transactional emails such as:\n- Account notifications\n- Password resets\n- Domain verification\n- Security alerts","ref":"Hackflare.Mailer.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hackflare.Mailer","doc":"email =\n      new()\n      |> to(\"user@example.com\")\n      |> from(\"noreply@hackflare.app\")\n      |> subject(\"Welcome to Hackflare\")\n      |> text_body(\"Welcome!\")\n\n    Hackflare.Mailer.deliver(email)","ref":"Hackflare.Mailer.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Hackflare.Mailer","doc":"In development, emails are stored locally and viewable at `/dev/mailbox`.\n\nIn production, configure the mailer adapter in `config/runtime.exs`:\n\n    config :hackflare, Hackflare.Mailer,\n      adapter: Swoosh.Adapters.Sendgrid,\n      api_key: System.get_env(\"SENDGRID_API_KEY\")\n\nSupported adapters include SendGrid, Mailgun, AWS SES, SMTP, and others.\nSee [Swoosh documentation](https://hexdocs.pm/swoosh) for available adapters.","ref":"Hackflare.Mailer.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Mailer.deliver/2","doc":"Delivers an email.\n\nIf the email is delivered it returns an `{:ok, result}` tuple. If it fails,\nreturns an `{:error, error}` tuple.","ref":"Hackflare.Mailer.html#deliver/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Mailer.deliver!/2","doc":"Delivers an email, raises on error.\n\nIf the email is delivered, it returns the result. If it fails, it raises\na `DeliveryError`.","ref":"Hackflare.Mailer.html#deliver!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Mailer.deliver_many/2","doc":"Delivers a list of emails.\n\nIt accepts a list of `%Swoosh.Email{}` as its first parameter.","ref":"Hackflare.Mailer.html#deliver_many/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Hackflare.Nameserver","doc":"Manages the DNS nameserver process and native Rust integration.\n\nThis GenServer acts as a bridge between the Elixir application and the Rust-based\nDNS nameserver implementation. It initializes and manages the lifetime of the native\nDNS manager, which handles all DNS query processing and zone management.","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Responsibilities - Hackflare.Nameserver","doc":"- Create and maintain the native DNS manager instance\n- Start the nameserver listening on the configured bind address and port\n- Handle GenServer lifecycle (start, stop, restart)\n- Provide interface to DNS operations via `Hackflare.Native`","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#module-responsibilities"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Hackflare.Nameserver","doc":"The nameserver is configured via the `:dns` application environment variable,\nwhich should contain:\n\n    config :hackflare,\n      dns: [\n        bind: \"0.0.0.0\",\n        port: 53\n      ]","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"module","title":"Native Integration - Hackflare.Nameserver","doc":"This module uses Rustler NIF bindings in `Hackflare.Native` to communicate with\nthe Rust nameserver implementation. The native manager handles the actual DNS\nprotocol parsing, zone storage, and query resolution.","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#module-native-integration"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Nameserver.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Nameserver.start_link/1","doc":"Starts the DNS nameserver GenServer.\n\nThis function is called by the supervisor to initialize the nameserver process.\nIt registers the process under the module name so it can be called globally.","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Nameserver.start_link/1","doc":"- `_opts` - Supervisor options (unused)","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#start_link/1-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Nameserver.start_link/1","doc":"- `{:ok, pid}` - PID of the started nameserver process\n  - `{:error, reason}` - If startup fails","ref":"Hackflare.Nameserver.html#start_link/1-returns"},{"type":"module","title":"Hackflare.Native","doc":"Rust NIF (Native Implemented Function) bindings for DNS operations.\n\nThis module provides Elixir bindings to the high-performance Rust DNS engine.\nAll DNS operations that are performance-critical are implemented in Rust and\nexposed through these NIF stubs. The actual implementation is in `native/core/src/`.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Manager Functions - Hackflare.Native","doc":"- `manager_new/0` - Create a new DNS manager instance\n- `manager_create_zone/2` - Create a new DNS zone\n- `manager_delete_zone/2` - Delete a DNS zone\n- `manager_list_zones/1` - List all zones in the manager","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#module-manager-functions"},{"type":"module","title":"Record Operations - Hackflare.Native","doc":"- `manager_add_record/6` - Add a DNS record to a zone\n- `manager_remove_record/4` - Remove a record from a zone\n- `manager_find_records/2` or `manager_find_records/3` - Query records by name and optional type","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#module-record-operations"},{"type":"module","title":"Query Handling - Hackflare.Native","doc":"- `engine_handle_query/2` - Process a raw DNS query and return response","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#module-query-handling"},{"type":"module","title":"Nameserver Control - Hackflare.Native","doc":"- `manager_start_nameserver/3` - Start the nameserver listening on bind:port","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#module-nameserver-control"},{"type":"module","title":"Error Handling - Hackflare.Native","doc":"If the native library is not loaded (e.g., in development without compilation),\nall functions raise `:nif_not_loaded` error. This is normal behavior and allows\nthe application to start in development environments.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#module-error-handling"},{"type":"module","title":"Performance - Hackflare.Native","doc":"These functions are designed to be fast. DNS query handling in particular uses\nRust's zero-copy capabilities for minimal memory allocation and maximum throughput.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#module-performance"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.engine_handle_query/2","doc":"Handles a raw DNS query and returns the response.\n\nProcesses an incoming DNS query packet and returns the appropriate response.\nThis is the core DNS query handling function used by the nameserver.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#engine_handle_query/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.engine_handle_query/2","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference\n  - `query` - Raw DNS query packet (typically binary data from the network)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#engine_handle_query/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.engine_handle_query/2","doc":"Raw DNS response packet (binary)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#engine_handle_query/2-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.engine_handle_query/2","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#engine_handle_query/2-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_add_record/6","doc":"Adds a DNS record to a zone.\n\nCreates a resource record in the specified zone. Multiple records with the same\nname but different types (or data) can coexist.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_add_record/6"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_add_record/6","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference\n  - `zone` - Zone name where the record will be added\n  - `name` - Record name (fully qualified domain name)\n  - `type` - DNS record type as atom (`:A`, `:AAAA`, `:CNAME`, `:MX`, `:TXT`, etc.)\n  - `ttl` - Time to live in seconds (non-negative integer)\n  - `data` - Record data (format depends on type, typically a string or list)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_add_record/6-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_add_record/6","doc":"`:ok` - Record added successfully\n  `{:error, reason}` - If addition fails (e.g., invalid type, zone not found)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_add_record/6-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_add_record/6","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_add_record/6-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_create_zone/2","doc":"Creates a new DNS zone in the manager.\n\nA zone represents a domain namespace (e.g., \"example.com\"). Records can be\nadded to the zone after creation.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_create_zone/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_create_zone/2","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference from `manager_new/0`\n  - `name` - Zone name as a string (e.g., \"example.com\")","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_create_zone/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_create_zone/2","doc":"`:ok` - Zone created successfully\n  `{:error, reason}` - If zone creation fails (e.g., zone already exists)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_create_zone/2-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_create_zone/2","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_create_zone/2-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_delete_zone/2","doc":"Deletes a DNS zone from the manager.\n\nRemoves the zone and all its associated records. This operation cannot be undone.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_delete_zone/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_delete_zone/2","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference\n  - `name` - Zone name to delete","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_delete_zone/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_delete_zone/2","doc":"`:ok` - Zone deleted successfully\n  `{:error, reason}` - If deletion fails (e.g., zone not found)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_delete_zone/2-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_delete_zone/2","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_delete_zone/2-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_find_records/3","doc":"Finds DNS records matching a name and optional type.\n\nQueries the manager for records. If a type is not specified, all record types\nmatching the name are returned.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_find_records/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_find_records/3","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference\n  - `name` - Record name to search for\n  - `type` - Optional: Specific record type to filter by (default: `nil` returns all types)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_find_records/3-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_find_records/3","doc":"List of matching records with their details\n  Empty list if no records found","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_find_records/3-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_find_records/3","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_find_records/3-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_list_zones/1","doc":"Lists all zones currently in the DNS manager.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_list_zones/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_list_zones/1","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_list_zones/1-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_list_zones/1","doc":"List of zone names (strings)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_list_zones/1-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_list_zones/1","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_list_zones/1-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_new/0","doc":"Creates a new DNS manager instance.\n\nThe manager is responsible for storing zones and handling DNS record operations.\nThis should typically be called once during application startup.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_new/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_new/0","doc":"Reference to the created DNS manager (opaque term)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_new/0-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_new/0","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_new/0-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_remove_record/4","doc":"Removes a DNS record from a zone.\n\nDeletes all records matching the specified name and type from the zone.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_remove_record/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_remove_record/4","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference\n  - `zone` - Zone name containing the record\n  - `name` - Record name to remove\n  - `type` - DNS record type (`:A`, `:AAAA`, `:CNAME`, etc.)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_remove_record/4-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_remove_record/4","doc":"`:ok` - Record removed successfully\n  `{:error, reason}` - If removal fails (e.g., record not found)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_remove_record/4-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_remove_record/4","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_remove_record/4-errors"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Native.manager_start_nameserver/3","doc":"Starts the DNS nameserver listening on the specified address and port.\n\nBegins listening for incoming DNS queries on UDP. This is a blocking operation\nthat runs in the background on the Rust side.","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_start_nameserver/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Hackflare.Native.manager_start_nameserver/3","doc":"- `mgr` - DNS manager reference\n  - `bind` - IP address to bind to (e.g., \"0.0.0.0\", \"127.0.0.1\")\n  - `port` - UDP port to listen on (typically 53 for DNS)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_start_nameserver/3-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Hackflare.Native.manager_start_nameserver/3","doc":"`:ok` - Nameserver started successfully\n  `{:error, reason}` - If startup fails (e.g., port already in use)","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_start_nameserver/3-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Errors - Hackflare.Native.manager_start_nameserver/3","doc":"`:nif_not_loaded` - If the native library is not compiled/loaded","ref":"Hackflare.Native.html#manager_start_nameserver/3-errors"},{"type":"module","title":"Hackflare.Repo","doc":"The Ecto Repository for Hackflare database operations.\n\nThis module provides the database connection and query interface for all\npersistent data in Hackflare. It uses PostgreSQL as the database backend\nand handles connection pooling, migrations, and Ecto query execution.","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Hackflare.Repo","doc":"# Query examples\n    Hackflare.Repo.all(MySchema)\n    Hackflare.Repo.get(MySchema, id)\n    Hackflare.Repo.insert(changeset)\n    Hackflare.Repo.update(changeset)\n    Hackflare.Repo.delete(changesetOrStruct)","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Hackflare.Repo","doc":"Database configuration is loaded from `config/runtime.exs` and environment variables:\n- `DATABASE_URL` - Full PostgreSQL connection string (typically used in production)\n- Or: `DB_HOST`, `DB_PORT`, `DB_NAME`, `DB_USER`, `DB_PASSWORD`","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"module","title":"Migrations - Hackflare.Repo","doc":"Run migrations with:\n\n    mix ecto.migrate\n\nCreate new migrations with:\n\n    mix ecto.gen.migration migration_name","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#module-migrations"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.aggregate/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.aggregate/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#aggregate/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.aggregate/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.aggregate/4 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#aggregate/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.all/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.all/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.all_by/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.all_by/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#all_by/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.checked_out?/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.checked_out?/0 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#checked_out?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.checkout/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.checkout/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#checkout/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.child_spec/1","doc":"","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.config/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.config/0 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#config/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.default_options/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.default_options/1 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#default_options/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.delete/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.delete!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete!/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#delete!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.delete_all/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete_all/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#delete_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.disconnect_all/2","doc":"Forces all connections in the repo pool to disconnect within the given interval.\n\nOnce this function is called, the pool will disconnect all of its connections\nas they are checked in or as they are pinged. Checked in connections will be\nrandomly disconnected within the given time interval. Pinged connections are\nimmediately disconnected - as they are idle (according to `:idle_interval`).\n\nIf the connection has a backoff configured (which is the case by default),\ndisconnecting means an attempt at a new connection will be done immediately\nafter, without starting a new process for each connection. However, if backoff\nhas been disabled, the connection process will terminate. In such cases,\ndisconnecting all connections may cause the pool supervisor to restart\ndepending on the max_restarts/max_seconds configuration of the pool,\nso you will want to set those carefully.","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#disconnect_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.exists?/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.exists?/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#exists?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.explain/3","doc":"Executes an EXPLAIN statement or similar for the given query according to its kind and the\nadapter in the given repository.","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#explain/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Hackflare.Repo.explain/3","doc":"# Postgres\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, Post)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\"\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.explain(Repo, :all, Post)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\"\n\n    # MySQL\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, from(p in Post, where: p.title == \"title\")) |> IO.puts()\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n    | id | select_type | table | partitions | type | possible_keys | key  | key_len | ref  | rows | filtered | Extra       |\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n    |  1 | SIMPLE      | p0    | NULL       | ALL  | NULL          | NULL | NULL    | NULL |    1 |    100.0 | Using where |\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n\n    # Shared opts\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, Post, analyze: true, timeout: 20_000)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=443) (actual time=0.013..0.013 rows=0 loops=1)\\nPlanning Time: 0.031 ms\\nExecution Time: 0.021 ms\"\n\nIt's safe to execute it for updates and deletes, no data change will be committed:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(Repo, :update_all, from(p in Post, update: [set: [title: \"new title\"]]))\n    \"Update on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=449)\\n  ->  Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=449)\"\n\nThis function is also available under the repository with name `explain`:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, from(p in Post, where: p.title == \"title\"))\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\\n  Filter: ((title)::text = 'title'::text)\"","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#explain/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Hackflare.Repo.explain/3","doc":"Built-in adapters support passing `opts` to the EXPLAIN statement according to the following:\n\nAdapter          | Supported opts\n---------------- | --------------\nPostgrex         | `analyze`, `verbose`, `costs`, `settings`, `buffers`, `timing`, `summary`, `format`, `plan`, `wrap_in_transaction`\nMyXQL            | `format`, `wrap_in_transaction`\n\nAll options except `format` are boolean valued and default to `false`.\n\nThe allowed `format` values are `:map`, `:yaml`, and `:text`:\n  * `:map` is the deserialized JSON encoding.\n  * `:yaml` and `:text` return the result as a string.\n\nThe built-in adapters support the following formats:\n  * Postgrex: `:map`, `:yaml` and `:text`\n  * MyXQL: `:map` and `:text`\n\nThe `wrap_in_transaction` option is a boolean that controls whether the command is run inside of a\ntransaction that is rolled back. This is useful when, for example, you'd like to use `analyze: true`\non an update or delete query without modifying data. Defaults to `true`.\n\nThe `:plan` option in Postgrex can take the values `:custom` or `:fallback_generic`. When `:custom`\nis specified, the explain plan generated will consider the specific values of the query parameters\nthat are supplied. When using `:fallback_generic`, the specific values of the query parameters will\nbe ignored. `:fallback_generic` does not use PostgreSQL's built-in support for a generic explain\nplan (available as of PostgreSQL 16), but instead uses a special implementation that works for PostgreSQL\nversions 12 and above. Defaults to `:custom`.\n\nAny other value passed to `opts` will be forwarded to the underlying adapter query function, including\nshared Repo options such as `:timeout`. Non built-in adapters may have specific behaviour and you should\nconsult their documentation for more details.\n\nFor version compatibility, please check your database's documentation:\n\n  * _Postgrex_: [PostgreSQL doc](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/sql-explain.html).\n  * _MyXQL_: [MySQL doc](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/explain.html).","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#explain/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.get/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.get!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get!/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#get!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.get_by/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_by/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#get_by/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.get_by!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_by!/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#get_by!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.get_dynamic_repo/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_dynamic_repo/0 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#get_dynamic_repo/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.in_transaction?/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.in_transaction?/0 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#in_transaction?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.insert/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#insert/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.insert!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert!/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#insert!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.insert_all/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_all/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#insert_all/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.insert_or_update/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_or_update/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#insert_or_update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.insert_or_update!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_or_update!/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#insert_or_update!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.load/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.load/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#load/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.one/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.one/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#one/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.one!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.one!/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#one!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.preload/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.preload/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#preload/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.prepare_query/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.prepare_query/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#prepare_query/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.prepare_transaction/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.prepare_transaction/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#prepare_transaction/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.put_dynamic_repo/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.put_dynamic_repo/1 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#put_dynamic_repo/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.query/3","doc":"Runs a custom SQL query.\n\nIf the query was successful, it will return an `:ok` tuple containing\na map with at least two keys:\n\n  * `:num_rows` - the number of rows affected\n  * `:rows` - the result set as a list. `nil` may be returned\n    instead of the list if the command does not yield any row\n    as result (but still yields the number of affected rows,\n    like a `delete` command without returning would)","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Hackflare.Repo.query/3","doc":"* `:log` - When false, does not log the query\n  * `:timeout` - Execute request timeout, accepts: `:infinity` (default: `15000`);","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Hackflare.Repo.query/3","doc":"iex> MyRepo.query(\"SELECT $1::integer + $2\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, %{rows: [[42]], num_rows: 1}}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.query(MyRepo, \"SELECT $1::integer + $2\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, %{rows: [[42]], num_rows: 1}}","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.query!/3","doc":"Same as `query/3` but returns result directly without `:ok` tuple\nand raises on invalid queries","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"Runs a custom SQL query that returns multiple results on the given repo.\n\nIn case of success, it must return an `:ok` tuple containing a list of\nmaps with at least two keys:\n\n  * `:num_rows` - the number of rows affected\n\n  * `:rows` - the result set as a list. `nil` may be returned\n    instead of the list if the command does not yield any row\n    as result (but still yields the number of affected rows,\n    like a `delete` command without returning would)","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query_many/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Hackflare.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"* `:log` - When false, does not log the query\n  * `:timeout` - Execute request timeout, accepts: `:infinity` (default: `15000`);","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query_many/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Hackflare.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"iex> MyRepo.query_many(\"SELECT $1; SELECT $2;\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, [%{rows: [[40]], num_rows: 1}, %{rows: [[2]], num_rows: 1}]}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.query_many(MyRepo, \"SELECT $1; SELECT $2;\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, [%{rows: [[40]], num_rows: 1}, %{rows: [[2]], num_rows: 1}]}","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query_many/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.query_many!/3","doc":"Same as `query_many/4` but returns result directly without `:ok` tuple\nand raises on invalid queries","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#query_many!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.reload/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.reload/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#reload/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.reload!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.reload!/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#reload!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.rollback/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.rollback/1 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#rollback/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.start_link/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.start_link/1 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.stop/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.stop/1 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#stop/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.stream/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.stream/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#stream/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.to_sql/2","doc":"Converts the given query to SQL according to its kind and the\nadapter in the given repository.","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#to_sql/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Hackflare.Repo.to_sql/2","doc":"The examples below are meant for reference. Each adapter will\nreturn a different result:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.to_sql(:all, Post)\n    {\"SELECT p.id, p.title, p.inserted_at, p.created_at FROM posts as p\", []}\n\n    iex> MyRepo.to_sql(:update_all, from(p in Post, update: [set: [title: ^\"hello\"]]))\n    {\"UPDATE posts AS p SET title = $1\", [\"hello\"]}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.to_sql(:all, MyRepo, Post)\n    {\"SELECT p.id, p.title, p.inserted_at, p.created_at FROM posts as p\", []}","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#to_sql/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.transact/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.transact/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#transact/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.transaction/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.transaction/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#transaction/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.update/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.update!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update!/2 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#update!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Hackflare.Repo.update_all/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update_all/3 .","ref":"Hackflare.Repo.html#update_all/3"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb","doc":"The entrypoint for defining your web interface and Phoenix components.\n\nThis module provides the common setup and helper functions for all web-layer components,\nincluding controllers, live views, templates, and components. It follows Phoenix conventions\nfor organizing HTTP handlers, real-time features, and UI components.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - HackflareWeb","doc":"Import this module in your web components:\n\n    use HackflareWeb, :controller\n    use HackflareWeb, :live_view\n    use HackflareWeb, :html\n    use HackflareWeb, :router","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - HackflareWeb","doc":"- **Controllers** - Handle HTTP requests and responses\n- **LiveViews** - Real-time interactive UI with WebSocket support\n- **Components** - Reusable UI elements built with Phoenix.Component\n- **Templates** - HTML5 templates with EEx templating\n- **Router** - HTTP routing and pipeline configuration","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Architecture - HackflareWeb","doc":"The web layer is layered as:\n1. **Endpoint** (`HackflareWeb.Endpoint`) - HTTP entry point\n2. **Router** (`HackflareWeb.Router`) - Route definitions and pipelines\n3. **Controllers** - Request handlers\n4. **Views/Components** - Response rendering\n5. **Templates** - HTML templates with interpolation\n\nStatic files are served from `priv/static/` and include assets built by esbuild (JS)\nand Tailwind (CSS).","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#module-architecture"},{"type":"macro","title":"HackflareWeb.__using__/1","doc":"When used, dispatch to the appropriate controller/live_view/etc.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#__using__/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.channel/0","doc":"Returns the setup for Phoenix channels.\n\nWhen used with `use HackflareWeb, :channel`, provides the base channel module\nfor WebSocket/long-polling connections.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#channel/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.channel/0","doc":"use HackflareWeb, :channel\n\n    def join(\"room:lobby\", _message, socket) do\n      {:ok, socket}\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#channel/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.controller/0","doc":"Returns the setup for controllers.\n\nWhen used with `use HackflareWeb, :controller`, provides common imports and\nconfiguration for HTTP request handlers supporting both HTML and JSON rendering.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#controller/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.controller/0","doc":"use HackflareWeb, :controller\n\n    def action(conn, _params) do\n      render(conn, :index, items: get_items())\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#controller/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.html/0","doc":"Returns the setup for HTML/component modules.\n\nWhen used with `use HackflareWeb, :html`, provides imports for building\nreusable HTML components and helpers.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#html/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.html/0","doc":"use HackflareWeb, :html\n\n    def my_component(assigns) do\n      ~H\" <%= @content %> \"\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#html/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.live_component/0","doc":"Returns the setup for LiveComponent modules.\n\nWhen used with `use HackflareWeb, :live_component`, provides configuration\nfor reusable stateful components within LiveView pages.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#live_component/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.live_component/0","doc":"use HackflareWeb, :live_component\n\n    def render(assigns) do\n      ~H\" <%= @label %> \"\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#live_component/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.live_view/0","doc":"Returns the setup for LiveView modules.\n\nWhen used with `use HackflareWeb, :live_view`, provides common configuration\nfor real-time interactive UI components with WebSocket support.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#live_view/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.live_view/0","doc":"use HackflareWeb, :live_view\n\n    def render(assigns) do\n      ~H\"\"\"\n       \n         \n          Count: <%= @count %>\n         \n       \n      \"\"\"\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#live_view/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.router/0","doc":"Returns the setup for routers.\n\nWhen used with `use HackflareWeb, :router`, provides common imports and\nconfiguration for HTTP routers.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#router/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.router/0","doc":"use HackflareWeb, :router\n\n    scope \"/\", MyApp do\n      pipe_through :browser\n      get \"/\", PageController, :index\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#router/0-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.static_paths/0","doc":"Returns the list of static file paths that should be served by the application.\n\nThese paths are served from the `priv/static` directory and include:\n- `assets/` - Compiled JavaScript and CSS\n- `fonts/` - Custom fonts\n- `images/` - Image assets\n- Standard files: favicon.ico, robots.txt","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#static_paths/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - HackflareWeb.static_paths/0","doc":"List of static file paths as strings","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#static_paths/0-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.verified_routes/0","doc":"Returns the setup for verified routes (the ~p sigil).\n\nWhen included in modules, enables the use of the verified routes sigil (~p)\nfor compile-time verified internal links. This prevents broken routes from\ncompiling.","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#verified_routes/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.verified_routes/0","doc":"~p\\\"/posts/#{post.id}\\\"\n    ~p\\\"/users?sort=name\\\"","ref":"HackflareWeb.html#verified_routes/0-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents","doc":"Provides core UI components.\n\nAt first glance, this module may seem daunting, but its goal is to provide\ncore building blocks for your application, such as tables, forms, and\ninputs. The components consist mostly of markup and are well-documented\nwith doc strings and declarative assigns. You may customize and style\nthem in any way you want, based on your application growth and needs.\n\nThe foundation for styling is Tailwind CSS, a utility-first CSS framework,\naugmented with daisyUI, a Tailwind CSS plugin that provides UI components\nand themes. Here are useful references:\n\n  * [daisyUI](https://daisyui.com/docs/intro/) - a good place to get\n    started and see the available components.\n\n  * [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com) - the foundational framework\n    we build on. You will use it for layout, sizing, flexbox, grid, and\n    spacing.\n\n  * [Heroicons](https://heroicons.com) - see `icon/1` for usage.\n\n  * [Phoenix.Component](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix_live_view/Phoenix.Component.html) -\n    the component system used by Phoenix. Some components, such as `<.link>`\n    and `<.form>`, are defined there.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","doc":"Renders a button with navigation support.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","doc":"<.button>Send!</.button>\n    <.button phx-click=\"go\" variant=\"primary\">Send!</.button>\n    <.button navigate={~p\"/\"}>Home</.button>","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","doc":"* `class` (`:any`)\n* `variant` (`:string`) - Must be one of `\"primary\"`.\n* Global attributes are accepted. Supports all globals plus: `[\"href\", \"navigate\", \"patch\", \"method\", \"download\", \"name\", \"value\", \"disabled\"]`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"Slots - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.button/1","doc":"* `inner_block` (required)","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#button/1-slots"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","doc":"Renders flash notices.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","doc":"<.flash kind={:info} flash={@flash} />\n    <.flash kind={:info} phx-mounted={show(\"#flash\")}>Welcome Back!</.flash>","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","doc":"* `id` (`:string`) - the optional id of flash container.\n* `flash` (`:map`) - the map of flash messages to display. Defaults to `%{}`.\n* `title` (`:string`) - Defaults to `nil`.\n* `kind` (`:atom`) - used for styling and flash lookup. Must be one of `:info`, or `:error`.\n* Global attributes are accepted. the arbitrary HTML attributes to add to the flash container.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"Slots - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.flash/1","doc":"* `inner_block` - the optional inner block that renders the flash message.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#flash/1-slots"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.header/1","doc":"Renders a header with title.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#header/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Slots - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.header/1","doc":"* `inner_block` (required)\n* `subtitle`\n* `actions`","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#header/1-slots"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.hide/2","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#hide/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.icon/1","doc":"Renders a [Heroicon](https://heroicons.com).\n\nHeroicons come in three styles – outline, solid, and mini.\nBy default, the outline style is used, but solid and mini may\nbe applied by using the `-solid` and `-mini` suffix.\n\nYou can customize the size and colors of the icons by setting\nwidth, height, and background color classes.\n\nIcons are extracted from the `deps/heroicons` directory and bundled within\nyour compiled app.css by the plugin in `assets/vendor/heroicons.js`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#icon/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.icon/1","doc":"<.icon name=\"hero-x-mark\" />\n    <.icon name=\"hero-arrow-path\" class=\"ml-1 size-3 motion-safe:animate-spin\" />","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#icon/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.icon/1","doc":"* `name` (`:string`) (required)\n* `class` (`:any`) - Defaults to `\"size-4\"`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#icon/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","doc":"Renders an input with label and error messages.\n\nA `Phoenix.HTML.FormField` may be passed as argument,\nwhich is used to retrieve the input name, id, and values.\nOtherwise all attributes may be passed explicitly.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Types - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","doc":"This function accepts all HTML input types, considering that:\n\n  * You may also set `type=\"select\"` to render a ` ` tag\n\n  * `type=\"checkbox\"` is used exclusively to render boolean values\n\n  * For live file uploads, see `Phoenix.Component.live_file_input/1`\n\nSee https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input\nfor more information. Unsupported types, such as radio, are best\nwritten directly in your templates.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-types"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","doc":"```heex\n<.input field={@form[:email]} type=\"email\" />\n<.input name=\"my-input\" errors={[\"oh no!\"]} />\n```","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Select type - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","doc":"When using `type=\"select\"`, you must pass the `options` and optionally\na `value` to mark which option should be preselected.\n\n```heex\n<.input field={@form[:user_type]} type=\"select\" options={[\"Admin\": \"admin\", \"User\": \"user\"]} />\n```\n\nFor more information on what kind of data can be passed to `options` see\n[`options_for_select`](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix_html/Phoenix.HTML.Form.html#options_for_select/2).","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-select-type"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.input/1","doc":"* `id` (`:any`) - Defaults to `nil`.\n* `name` (`:any`)\n* `label` (`:string`) - Defaults to `nil`.\n* `value` (`:any`)\n* `type` (`:string`) - Defaults to `\"text\"`. Must be one of `\"checkbox\"`, `\"color\"`, `\"date\"`, `\"datetime-local\"`, `\"email\"`, `\"file\"`, `\"month\"`, `\"number\"`, `\"password\"`, `\"search\"`, `\"select\"`, `\"tel\"`, `\"text\"`, `\"textarea\"`, `\"time\"`, `\"url\"`, `\"week\"`, or `\"hidden\"`.\n* `field` (`Phoenix.HTML.FormField`) - a form field struct retrieved from the form, for example: @form[:email].\n* `errors` (`:list`) - Defaults to `[]`.\n* `checked` (`:boolean`) - the checked flag for checkbox inputs.\n* `prompt` (`:string`) - the prompt for select inputs. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `options` (`:list`) - the options to pass to Phoenix.HTML.Form.options_for_select/2.\n* `multiple` (`:boolean`) - the multiple flag for select inputs. Defaults to `false`.\n* `class` (`:any`) - the input class to use over defaults. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `error_class` (`:any`) - the input error class to use over defaults. Defaults to `nil`.\n* Global attributes are accepted. Supports all globals plus: `[\"accept\", \"autocomplete\", \"capture\", \"cols\", \"disabled\", \"form\", \"list\", \"max\", \"maxlength\", \"min\", \"minlength\", \"multiple\", \"pattern\", \"placeholder\", \"readonly\", \"required\", \"rows\", \"size\", \"step\"]`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#input/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.list/1","doc":"Renders a data list.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.list/1","doc":"<.list>\n      <:item title=\"Title\">{@post.title}</:item>\n      <:item title=\"Views\">{@post.views}</:item>\n    </.list>","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#list/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Slots - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.list/1","doc":"* `item` (required) - Accepts attributes:\n\n  * `title` (`:string`) (required)","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#list/1-slots"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.show/2","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#show/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","doc":"Renders a table with generic styling.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","doc":"<.table id=\"users\" rows={@users}>\n      <:col :let={user} label=\"id\">{user.id}</:col>\n      <:col :let={user} label=\"username\">{user.username}</:col>\n    </.table>","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","doc":"* `id` (`:string`) (required)\n* `rows` (`:list`) (required)\n* `row_id` (`:any`) - the function for generating the row id. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `row_click` (`:any`) - the function for handling phx-click on each row. Defaults to `nil`.\n* `row_item` (`:any`) - the function for mapping each row before calling the :col and :action slots. Defaults to `&Function.identity/1`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"Slots - HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.table/1","doc":"* `col` (required) - Accepts attributes:\n\n  * `label` (`:string`)\n* `action` - the slot for showing user actions in the last table column.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#table/1-slots"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.translate_error/1","doc":"Translates an error message using gettext.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#translate_error/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.translate_errors/2","doc":"Translates the errors for a field from a keyword list of errors.","ref":"HackflareWeb.CoreComponents.html#translate_errors/2"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.broadcast/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast/3 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast/3"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.broadcast!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast!/3 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.broadcast_from/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast_from/4 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast_from/4"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.broadcast_from!/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast_from!/4 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast_from!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.call/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns the child specification to start the endpoint\nunder a supervision tree.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.config/2","doc":"Returns the endpoint configuration for `key`\n\nReturns `default` if the key does not exist.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#config/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.config_change/2","doc":"Reloads the configuration given the application environment changes.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#config_change/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.host/0","doc":"Returns the host for the given endpoint.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#host/0"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.init/1 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.local_broadcast/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.local_broadcast/3 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#local_broadcast/3"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.local_broadcast_from/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.local_broadcast_from/4 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#local_broadcast_from/4"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.path/1","doc":"Generates the path information when routing to this endpoint.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#path/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.script_name/0","doc":"Generates the script name.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#script_name/0"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.server_info/1","doc":"Returns the address and port that the server is running on","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#server_info/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.start_link/1","doc":"Starts the endpoint supervision tree.\n\nAll other options are merged into the endpoint configuration.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.static_integrity/1","doc":"Generates a base64-encoded cryptographic hash (sha512) to a static file\nin `priv/static`. Meant to be used for Subresource Integrity with CDNs.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#static_integrity/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.static_lookup/1","doc":"Returns a two item tuple with the first item being the `static_path`\nand the second item being the `static_integrity`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#static_lookup/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.static_path/1","doc":"Generates a route to a static file in `priv/static`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#static_path/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.static_url/0","doc":"Generates the static URL without any path information.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:static_url` to generate\nsuch. It falls back to `:url` if `:static_url` is not set.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#static_url/0"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.struct_url/0","doc":"Generates the endpoint base URL but as a `URI` struct.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:url` to generate such.\nUseful for manipulating the URL data and passing it to\nURL helpers.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#struct_url/0"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.subscribe/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.subscribe/2 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#subscribe/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.unsubscribe/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.unsubscribe/1 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#unsubscribe/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.url/0","doc":"Generates the endpoint base URL without any path information.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:url` to generate such.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Endpoint.html#url/0"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.ErrorHTML","doc":"This module is invoked by your endpoint in case of errors on HTML requests.\n\nSee config/config.exs.","ref":"HackflareWeb.ErrorHTML.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.ErrorHTML.404/1","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.ErrorHTML.html#404/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.ErrorHTML.render/2","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.ErrorHTML.html#render/2"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.ErrorJSON","doc":"This module is invoked by your endpoint in case of errors on JSON requests.\n\nSee config/config.exs.","ref":"HackflareWeb.ErrorJSON.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.ErrorJSON.render/2","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.ErrorJSON.html#render/2"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.Gettext","doc":"A module providing Internationalization with a gettext-based API.\n\nBy using [Gettext](https://hexdocs.pm/gettext), your module compiles translations\nthat you can use in your application. To use this Gettext backend module,\ncall `use Gettext` and pass it as an option:\n\n    use Gettext, backend: HackflareWeb.Gettext\n\n    # Simple translation\n    gettext(\"Here is the string to translate\")\n\n    # Plural translation\n    ngettext(\"Here is the string to translate\",\n             \"Here are the strings to translate\",\n             3)\n\n    # Domain-based translation\n    dgettext(\"errors\", \"Here is the error message to translate\")\n\nSee the [Gettext Docs](https://hexdocs.pm/gettext) for detailed usage.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.handle_missing_bindings/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Gettext.Backend.handle_missing_bindings/2 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.html#handle_missing_bindings/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.handle_missing_plural_translation/7","doc":"Callback implementation for  Gettext.Backend.handle_missing_plural_translation/7 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.html#handle_missing_plural_translation/7"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.handle_missing_translation/5","doc":"Callback implementation for  Gettext.Backend.handle_missing_translation/5 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Gettext.html#handle_missing_translation/5"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts","doc":"This module holds layouts and related functionality\nused by your application.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.app/1","doc":"Renders your app layout.\n\nThis function is typically invoked from every template,\nand it often contains your application menu, sidebar,\nor similar.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#app/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.Layouts.app/1","doc":"Content","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#app/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.Layouts.app/1","doc":"* `flash` (`:map`) (required) - the map of flash messages.\n* `current_scope` (`:map`) - the current [scope](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix/scopes.html). Defaults to `nil`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#app/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"Slots - HackflareWeb.Layouts.app/1","doc":"* `inner_block` (required)","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#app/1-slots"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.auth_menu/1","doc":"Provides a redir to dashboard. Replace current icon with signed in icon in future.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#auth_menu/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.Layouts.auth_menu/1","doc":"* `current_scope` (`:map`) - the current [scope](https://hexdocs.pm/phoenix/scopes.html). Defaults to `nil`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#auth_menu/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.flash_group/1","doc":"Shows the flash group with standard titles and content.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#flash_group/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - HackflareWeb.Layouts.flash_group/1","doc":"<.flash_group flash={@flash} />","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#flash_group/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.Layouts.flash_group/1","doc":"* `flash` (`:map`) (required) - the map of flash messages.\n* `id` (`:string`) - the optional id of flash container. Defaults to `\"flash-group\"`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#flash_group/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.home/1","doc":"Renders the homepage content using the app layout.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#home/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Attributes - HackflareWeb.Layouts.home/1","doc":"* `flash` (`:map`) - the map of flash messages. Defaults to `%{}`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#home/1-attributes"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.root/1","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#root/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.theme_toggle/1","doc":"Provides dark vs light theme toggle based on themes defined in app.css.\n\nSee   in root.html.heex which applies the theme before page load.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Layouts.html#theme_toggle/1"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.PageController","doc":"Controller for static pages in the Hackflare web application.\n\nThis controller handles basic page requests such as the home page.\nFor dynamic, real-time pages, use LiveView modules instead.","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.PageController.home/2","doc":"Render the home page.\n\nThis is the landing page for users visiting the Hackflare application.\nIt displays information about the service and entry points for authentication.","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageController.html#home/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - HackflareWeb.PageController.home/2","doc":"- `conn` - The Plug.Conn connection struct\n  - `_params` - Query parameters (unused)","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageController.html#home/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - HackflareWeb.PageController.home/2","doc":"Renders the `home.html` template.","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageController.html#home/2-returns"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.PageHTML","doc":"This module contains pages rendered by PageController.\n\nSee the `page_html` directory for all templates available.","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageHTML.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.PageHTML.render/2","doc":"Renders the home page using the Layouts.home component.\n\nDelegates to the Layouts module for rendering the homepage with standard\nnavigation and layout structure.","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageHTML.html#render/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - HackflareWeb.PageHTML.render/2","doc":"- `\"home.html\"` - Template name\n  - `assigns` - Assigns map containing variables for the template","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageHTML.html#render/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - HackflareWeb.PageHTML.render/2","doc":"Rendered HTML output","ref":"HackflareWeb.PageHTML.html#render/2-returns"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.Router","doc":"HTTP Router for Hackflare web application.\n\nThis module defines all HTTP routes and request pipelines for the Hackflare\nweb interface. Routes are matched against incoming HTTP requests and dispatched\nto the appropriate controller or live view handler.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Pipelines - HackflareWeb.Router","doc":"Pipelines are sequences of plugs that process requests before they reach handlers.\n\n### :browser\n\nUsed for traditional HTML requests. Includes:\n- CSRF protection\n- Session handling\n- LiveView flash support\n- Secure headers\n\n### :api\n\nUsed for JSON API requests. Includes:\n- JSON content type handling\n- No CSRF/session requirements","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#module-pipelines"},{"type":"module","title":"Routes - HackflareWeb.Router","doc":"Currently defined routes:\n- `GET /` - Home page (PageController.home)\n- `/dev/dashboard` - LiveDashboard (development only)\n- `/dev/mailbox` - Email preview (development only)","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#module-routes"},{"type":"module","title":"Development-only Routes - HackflareWeb.Router","doc":"The `/dev` scope is only mounted when `dev_routes` is enabled in compile-time\nconfiguration. This provides development tools:\n- LiveDashboard for monitoring and debugging\n- Swoosh mailbox preview for email testing","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#module-development-only-routes"},{"type":"module","title":"Extending Routes - HackflareWeb.Router","doc":"To add new routes:\n\n    scope \"/api/v1\", HackflareWeb do\n      pipe_through :api\n      resources \"/domains\", DomainController\n    end","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#module-extending-routes"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Router.api/2","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#api/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Router.browser/2","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#browser/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Router.call/2","doc":"Callback invoked by Plug on every request.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Router.formatted_routes/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.VerifiedRoutes.formatted_routes/1 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#formatted_routes/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Router.init/1","doc":"Callback required by Plug that initializes the router\nfor serving web requests.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Router.verified_route?/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.VerifiedRoutes.verified_route?/2 .","ref":"HackflareWeb.Router.html#verified_route?/2"},{"type":"module","title":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry","doc":"","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.metrics/0","doc":"Returns the list of metrics to be monitored by the telemetry system.\n\nIncludes metrics for:\n- Phoenix HTTP endpoints and routing\n- Phoenix LiveView channels\n- Erlang VM memory usage and scheduler metrics\n\nThese metrics can be exported to monitoring services or displayed in\nthe LiveDashboard during development.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html#metrics/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - HackflareWeb.Telemetry.metrics/0","doc":"List of `Telemetry.Metrics` metric definitions","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html#metrics/0-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.start_link/1","doc":"Starts the Telemetry supervisor.\n\nThis function initializes the telemetry supervision tree, which manages\nperiodic measurements and metric collection for the application.","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - HackflareWeb.Telemetry.start_link/1","doc":"- `arg` - Arguments passed from the supervisor","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html#start_link/1-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - HackflareWeb.Telemetry.start_link/1","doc":"- `{:ok, pid}` - PID of the telemetry supervisor\n  - `{:error, reason}` - If startup fails","ref":"HackflareWeb.Telemetry.html#start_link/1-returns"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}